West Imperial Terminal,
To know it is to love it.
Los Angeles International (LAX) is one of the busiest air-
ports in the world.
And unbeknownst to many people,
there's a convenient, comfortable, uncrowded terminal
right inside the big turmoil. There's lots of parking
space here. No traffic problems. No kidding! West Impe-
rial Terminal is its name... because it's west on Imperial
Highway (NOT Century Boulevard).
Overseas Charter
Flights use West Imperial Terminal and so does Holiday
Airlines (we're the only scheduled airline that does).
Why does Holiday Airlines use West Imperial Terminal?
Because it's convenient, comfortable and uncrowded,
that's why.
Holiday Airlines serves Lake Tahoe via South Lake Tahoe (California)
Airport -
TVL.
Yuk!
